Clearly not. The creature merely whistled and tried to charge straight at Thassalin. Fortunately, despite its size, it was agile enough to dodge, but Nyssi couldn't help but scream when she almost lost her grip on its overly smooth scales.
"HOW DO WE KILL THEM ?", cried Nyssi.
"AIM FOR THEIR HEADS !"
"THIS WON'T BE EASY !"
Thassalin exhaled, then circled around to get closer to the mountain he called his home. The black beast followed, somewhat panicked when a bolt of fire struck her from behind. The creature hadn't noticed she was no longer alone. Its panic grew when Thassalin slowed down, then violently hit her head with his tail, knocking her off course.
Groaning and whistling, the creature took to the air and spat into the air. Suddenly, everything became black, as if the monster was sucking the light from the sky and replacing it with a cloud of eternal night.
With no visibility left, Thassalin tried to retreat, but crashed into the tree tops before crashing into the clearing. As if she had known exactly where he had fallen, the creature charged straight at him, dragging the dark cloud in its wake.
"Kayel !", exclaimed Tenuk as he pulled himself out of the cloud and began circling to try to spot Nyssi and Thassalin below in the darkness. "What are we doing, Kayel ? Kayel... ? Kayel, where are you ?"
Below, Nyssi struggled to her feet. She was sure she had broken something, but her strange, unnatural healing powers had already started to take effect. One couldn't say the same for Thassalin, who was lying on a mound, leaning against the only tree that hadn't bent under his weight. Nyssi tried her best to reach Thassalin, but she couldn't see two meters ahead. Everything was plunged into darkness, swallowed by impious shadows. And within these shadows, something howled.
A horrible club-like tail came crashing down beside Nyssi, knocking her backward. She noticed, however, that the tail was moving, not targeting her. The creature, from what Nyssi could see and hear, was growling and clawing at the shadows it had created. Something was teleporting through the darkness, striking the monster, disorienting it.
A shot rang out suddenly, and the monster collapsed in silence, inert. The darkness surrounding them dissipated, revealing what had happened. Standing over the creature was Kayel, holding the rifle and breathing heavily.
"It's... the strangest shadow jump I've ever made... Thanto kat'olon...", panted Kayel. His eyes glowed with a black light, and a dark energy coursed through his body. However, as he spoke, the organic plating of Kayel regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow.
It took Nyssi a moment to understand what had happened. They all knew that Kayel possessed strange shadow powers. He used them rarely, as most people considered them impious and rather frightening. But Nyssi didn't know that Kayel could use these powers in the dark. And, judging by his behavior, Kayel seemed surprised himself.
"Are you okay?" Nyssi couldn't help but ask.
"Yes, I'm fine. I killed something. It'll be better in a minute." Kayel examined his work, while Tenuk made his way to land beside him, reverting to his normal Spast form.
Maintenant que la créature ne bougeait plus, ils pouvaient mieux voir de quoi il s'agissait. Sa peau était noire comme du charbon et gluante, mais la bave continuait d'adhérer à son corps. Elle avait quatre ailes et quatre membres, qui se terminaient tous par de longues serres, et deux cornes droites sortaient de son crâne.
Avant que Tenuk et Kayel puissent demander ce qu'était ce truc, quelque chose hurla et s'élança d'un buisson voisin. Cependant, la bête n'eut pas le temps de les atteindre, car un véhicule familier s'écrasa dans son flanc, la projetant aux pieds de Nyssi. Ne prenant aucun risque, cette dernière attrapa son fusil et lui tira aussitôt dans le crâne, tuant la créature sur le coup.
"Oups...", marmonna Retvik du siège conducteur, avant de couper maladroitement le moteur et de sauter du camion. "Je, euh, ne voulais pas faire ça. Vous allez bien ?"
"Tu as pratiquement loupé toute l'action", regretta Tenuk. "Tu étais où ?"
"Vous m'avez tous lâché. Je suis venu ici aussi vite que j'ai pu", soupira Retvik. "Peut-on savoir ce que sont ces choses ignobles ?"
L'interrogation de Retvik reçut heureusement une réponse de Thassalin, qui venait de se relever. Il était tout coupé et griffé de partout et semblait un peu déboussolé, mais il n'avait pas l'air d'être trop blessé.
"VOUS AVEZ TUÉ LES CORRUPTIIDS ! LES MONSTRES INFECTÉS. DES CRÉATURES LAISSÉES ICI LORSQUE LA CORRUPTION A ATTAQUÉ VOS DIEUX."
"Tu veux dire... l'horrible monstre dieu que nous avons... aidé à tuer ?", bégaya Tenuk.
"OUI. TOUT À FAIT. IL Y EN A PEUT-ÊTRE D'AUTRES, MAIS JE N'AI PAS RÉUSSI À LES VISER À LA TÊTE. IL ME MANQUE UN FUSIL. EN PLUS, DEUX CONTRE UN, CE N'EST PAS JUSTE, NON ?" Thassalin se dirigea vers Kayel et lui tapota la tête. "MERCI, PETIT. TU ME RAPPELLES MON VIEIL AMI ARKADIN. MAIS EN MOINS MEURTRIER ET MOINS CAPABLE DE TUER DES UNIVERS."
"Euh... merci... je suppose", dit Kayel avec un haussement d'épaules. "Donc, on a fini, ici ?"
Nissy shrugged her shoulders, then picked up her camera to photograph the beasts, now surely dead. She then took out her favorite dagger, the dagger of the god of death, and began cutting off one of the creature's horns, before moving on to the other. But as she finished, the creatures caught fire and quickly turned into piles of ashes. The same thing happened to the horns that Nyssi had cut off.
"Well... it's both convenient and inconvenient at the same time," she sighed. "At least I still have the photos..."
